HEADWORD: Glume
<hw>Glume</hw> <pr>(gl⟦umac⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>gluma</ets> hull, husk, fr. <ets>glubere</ets> to bark or peel: cf.
F. <ets>glume</ets> or <ets>gloume</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The bracteal covering of the flowers or seeds of grain and grasses;
esp., an outer husk or bract of a spikelet.</def>
<rj><au>Gray.</au></rj></p>

